        <h2 class="__m-h2">Architecture</h2>

        <h3 class="__m-h3">MVC</h3>

        <p>It's a simple MVC architecture. You can easily code your features in the <code class="__c-single">controllers</code> folders and render the HTML in the <code class="__c-single">views</code> folder.</p>

        <hr>

        <h2 class="__m-h2">Configuration</h2>

        <h3 class="__m-h3">config.json</h3>

        <p>You can easily configure and edit you app with the <code class="__c-single">config.json</code> file in <code class="__c-single">./core/config</code> folder. Example of entry :</p>

        <div class="__c-code-block">
            <code><pre>"development": {
    "config_id": "development", //Don't touch
    "host": "localhost:3000", //Your Node.js host
    "domain": "localhost",
    "app_name": "Your app name",
    "app_desc": "Your app description",
    "root": "http://localhost:3000",
    "app_port": 3000,
    "db": "[URL OF THE DB]"
  },</pre>
            </code>
        </div>

        <p class="__m-margin-b">Retrieve this configuration in the global variable <code class="__c-single">global.CONFIG_CURRENT</code> and use it in the entire app.</p>

        <p>You can also edit the <code class="__c-single">ecosystem.config.js</code> to run the app on production mode.</p>

        <p></p>

        <h3 class="__m-h3">Server</h3>

        <p class="__m-margin-b-2x">The server & bin configuration are in <code class="__c-single">./bin/app.js</code>.</p>

